ering%20my%20home%20of%2017%20years%20showed%20me%20my%20'poverty%20mentality'%20has%20been%20doing%20me%20more%20harm%20than%20good%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20offers%20and%20details%20on%20this%20page%20may%20have%20updated%20or%20changed%20since%20the%20time%20of%20publication.%20See%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecluttering-my-home-poverty-mentality-harms-2024-03%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20current%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20links%20for%20the%20products%20on%20this%20page%20are%20from%20partners%20that%20compensate%20us%20and%20terms%20apply%20to%20offers%20listed%20(see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Four-partners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertiser%20disclosure%20with%20our%20list%20of%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20details).%20However%2C%20our%20opinions%20are%20our%20own.%20See%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-finance-editorial-standards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20products%20and%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20you%20make%20smart%20decisions%20with%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mccamy%20wife%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e666927fee23d78754f3c72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20right%2C%20with%20her%20wife.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Laura%20McCamy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAt%20the%20urging%20of%20my%20sister-in-law%2C%20I%20finally%20decluttered%20my%20home%20of%2017%20years%20recently.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20getting%20rid%20of%20things%2C%20even%20if%20they%20no%20longer%20made%20sense%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMy%20'poverty%20mentality'%20was%20holding%20me%20back%2C%20but%20getting%20rid%20of%20those%20items%20freed%20up%20mental%20and%20physical%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202004%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20moved%20from%20a%201%2C200-square-foot%20flat%20full%20of%20belongings%20into%20an%20800-square-foot%20condo.%20I%20had%20done%20a%20huge%20declutter%20at%20our%20old%20place%20before%20we%20moved%2C%20so%20I%20was%20confident%20that%20I%20could%20keep%20my%20clutter%20to%20a%20minimum%20in%20a%20smaller%20space.%20But%20I%20hadn't%20dealt%20with%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20factors%20underlying%20my%20hoarding%20instincts%3A%20poverty%20mentality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeventeen%20years%20later%2C%20I%20had%20to%20confront%20this%20issue%20to%20create%20a%20comfortable%20living%20space.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20'poverty%20mentality'%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20define%20poverty%20mentality%20as%20living%20in%20unnecessary%20scarcity%20and%20fear.%20It%20leads%20me%20to%20make%20poor%20decisions%20about%20the%20possessions%20I%20bring%20into%20my%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scarcity%20mindset%20gives%20me%20an%20excuse%20to%20hang%20onto%20random%20possessions.%20Yes%2C%20perhaps%20the%20item%20is%20broken%20or%20ugly%2C%20or%20it%20doesn't%20fit%20me%20or%20our%20house%2C%20but%20my%20poverty%20mentality%20tells%20me%20that%20I%20need%20to%20keep%20it%20because%20I%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20another.%20That%20belief%20has%20led%20me%20to%20hang%20onto%20clothes%20that%20don't%20fit%20(even%20though%20I%20have%20plenty%20of%20clothes%20that%20do%20fit)%20and%20furniture%20I%20don't%20need.%20And%20looking%20for%20bargains%20can%20lead%20me%20to%20spend%20more%20on%20a%20bunch%20of%20cheap%20stuff%20that%20doesn't%20meet%20my%20needs%20than%20I%20would%20on%20one%20pricier%20item%20that%20is%20exactly%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20became%20aware%20of%20this%20pattern%20when%20I%20bought%20a%20new%20couch%20in%202001.%20I%20had%20never%20owned%20a%20new%20sofa%20before%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I'd%20never%20bought%20a%20piece%20of%20furniture%20new%20other%20than%20mattresses.%20The%20price%20was%20%24750%2C%20which%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20me%20back%20then.%20But%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20could%20spend%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20on%20random%2C%20marginally%20useful%20items%20from%20the%20thrift%20store%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20I'd%20get%20more%20satisfaction%20from%20the%20couch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20sofa%20was%20a%20revelation.%20When%20I%20sat%20on%20it%2C%20the%20springs%20were%20firm%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20sink%20between%20the%20cushions%2C%20something%20I%20didn't%20realize%20was%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couch%2C%20covered%20in%20swirly%20patterned%20purple%20velvet%2C%20is%20still%20in%20our%20living%20room.%20Now%2C%20I%20do%20sink%20into%20the%20cushions%2C%20and%20it's%20finally%20time%20to%20replace%20it%2C%20but%20the%20scarcity%20mindset%20is%20hard%20to%20shake.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20cat%20lounges%20on%20a%20purple%20velvet%20couch%20in%20front%20of%20a%20window%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F615c5c3d1725d20018b7ca28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20swirly%20purple%20velvet%20couch.%3Cp%3ELaura%20McCamy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20have%20comfortable%20salaries%2C%20and%20with%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20can%20afford%20to%20buy%20nice%20furniture%2C%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20house%20was%20still%20full%20of%20freebies%20and%20stuff%20that%20wasn't%20working%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%20until%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChanging%20my%20attitude%20was%20hard%20at%20first%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20visit%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20my%20wife's%20sister%20took%20one%20look%20at%20our%20overstuffed%20living%20space%20and%20offered%20to%20come%20back%20and%20help%20us%20declutter%20and%20reorganize%20our%20home.%20She%20is%20a%20minimalist%20and%20a%20designer%2C%20so%20she%20had%20lots%20of%20ideas%20about%20making%20the%20space%20work%20better%20for%20us.%20She%20was%20finally%20able%20to%20help%20us%20this%20August%2C%20a%20visit%20I%20anticipated%20with%20excitement%20and%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20dread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20response%20to%20every%20suggestion%20she%20had%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20stuff%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BNo!%26quot%3B%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20part%20with%20shelves%20left%20behind%20by%20the%20unit's%20previous%20owner%2C%20a%20rolltop%20desk%20that%20was%20far%20too%20big%20for%20our%20living%20room%2C%20or%20a%20table%20a%20neighbor%20had%20given%20us%20when%20they%20moved%20that%20had%20been%20disassembled%20and%20gathering%20dust%20for%20years.%20It%20broke%20my%20heart%20to%20give%20up%20kitchen%20items%2C%20especially%20the%20handmade%20pottery%20I%20had%20collected%20at%20craft%20shows%20over%20the%20years%2C%20even%20the%20pieces%20that%20were%20chipped%20and%20didn't%20fit%20into%20our%20cabinets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20we%20filled%20boxes%20for%20Goodwill%2C%20sold%20pieces%20of%20furniture%2C%20and%20rearranged%20what%20was%20left%2C%20I%20warmed%20to%20the%20project.%20The%20things%20I%20was%20hanging%20onto%20were%20a%20larger%20burden%20than%20I%20realized.%20Pants%20that%20no%20longer%20fit%20were%20asking%20me%20when%20I%20was%20going%20to%20lose%20those%2010%20pounds.%20The%20books%20gathering%20dust%20wondered%20why%20I%20hadn't%20read%20them%20yet.%20Giving%20those%20items%20away%20opened%20up%20space%20in%20my%20head%20as%20well%20as%20my%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20even%20become%20willing%20to%20give%20up%20my%20beloved%20yellow%20Formica%20and%20chrome%20kitchen%20table%20and%20the%20red%20vinyl%20matching%20chairs.%20We%20must%20put%20a%20kitchen%20island%20in%20their%20place%20for%20much-needed%20storage%20and%20counter%20space%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20island%20can%20be%20yellow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI've%20now%20learned%20that%20less%20is%20more%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20bigger%20unit%20in%20our%20complex%20was%20up%20for%20sale%2C%20and%20we%20thought%20about%20buying%20it%20to%20have%20more%20space.%20But%20my%20wife's%20sister%20told%20us%20that%20our%20place%20was%20bigger%20than%20we%20thought%2C%20and%20she%20was%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20hulking%20furniture%20that%20we%20were%20sure%20we%20needed%2C%20our%20space%20feels%20lighter%20and%20airier.%20We%20replaced%20our%20freebie%20coffee%20table%20with%20a%20beautiful%20brand-new%20table%20that%20includes%20a%20storage%20space.%20We%20repaired%20an%20antique%20armoire%20(one%20of%20the%20only%20pieces%20our%20mentor%20let%20us%20keep)%2C%20and%20our%20new%20couch%20will%20arrive%20someday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20have%20both%20worked%20very%20hard%20to%20advance%20our%20careers.%20But%20my%20poverty%20mentality%20kept%20me%20living%20as%20though%20I%20were%20barely%20employed%20and%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck.%20It%20kept%20me%20from%20thoroughly%20enjoying%20and%20inhabiting%20my%20living%20space%20and%20dragged%20me%20down%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20all%20the%20possessions%20I%20had%20to%20manage%20and%20organize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorse%2C%20the%20mindset%20that%20leads%20me%20to%20hang%20onto%20stuff%20costs%20me%20money.%20For%20example%2C%20as%20I%20decluttered%20this%20summer%2C%20I%20found%20a%20pair%20of%20glasses%20that%20I%20misplaced%20over%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20buried%20in%20a%20pile%20of%20books.%20I%20had%20just%20bought%20another%20pair%20to%20replace%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20not%20always%20about%20spending%20less%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20attitudes%20about%20spending%20money%20are%20generational.%20My%20parents%20grew%20up%20during%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20and%20they%20have%20continued%20to%20scrimp%20and%20save%20and%20worry%20that%20they%20would%20end%20up%20on%20the%20street%2C%20even%20though%20they%20have%20a%20generous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E%20income.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20was%20too%20cold%20for%20them%20to%20get%20out%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%20one%20winter.%20The%20friendly%20local%20health%20food%20store%20owner%20would%20have%20dropped%20off%20groceries%2C%20but%20their%20prices%20were%20higher%20than%20the%20chain%20supermarket%20in%20the%20next%20town%2C%20so%20my%20parents%20skipped%20meals%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20it's%20time%20for%20me%20to%20take%20a%20different%20path%20around%20finances%20than%20my%20parents.%20The%20opposite%20of%20my%20poverty%20mentality%20isn't%20to%20act%20like%20I'm%20rich%20(I'm%20not)%20or%20spend%20every%20dime%20I%20make.%20I%20will%20still%20look%20for%20bargains%20and%20ways%20to%20cut%20corners.%20But%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20organizing%20my%20home%2C%20I%20am%20willing%20to%20spend%20a%20bit%20to%20own%20beautiful%2C%20functional%20items%20that%20bring%20me%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20view%20the%20act%20of%20giving%20away%20things%20that%20no%20longer%20work%20for%20me%20as%20a%20form%20of%20self-care%20rather%20than%20an%20admission%20of%20failure.%20The%20money%20it%20takes%20to%20create%20a%20harmonious%20living%20space%20is%20well-spent.%20After%20all%2C%20what%20is%20money%20for%20but%20to%20help%20us%20live%20happily%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20wit