20the%20party%20has%20named%20former%20MLA%20Pradeep%20Purohit%20from%20Bargarh%2C%20axing%20sitting%20MP%20Suresh%20Pujari.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Malvika%20Keshari%20Deo%2C%20wife%20of%20the%20scion%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20Kalahandi%20royal%20family%20and%20former%20Kalahandi%20MP%20Arka%20Keshari%20Deo%2C%20has%20eased%20out%20incumbent%20Basanta%20Panda%20in%20the%20Kalahandi%20seat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20sources%20said%20that%20the%20party%20will%20announce%20its%20candidates%20for%20the%20other%20three%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20and%20147%20assembly%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJD%2C%20which%20has%20ruled%20the%20state%20for%20the%20last%2024%20years%20(including%20nearly%20nine%20years%20in%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJP)%2C%20is%20also%20in%20the%20final%20stages%20of%20clearing%20its%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20both%20the%20state%20assembly%20and%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20the%20alliance%20talks%20succeeded%2C%20the%20two%20parties%2C%20which%20are%20currently%20the%20main%20political%20rivals%20in%20the%20state%2C%20would%20have%20formed%20a%20poll%20partnership%20after%20a%20gap%20of%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20alliance%20talks%2C%20which%20began%20in%20earnest%20soon%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20March%205%20visit%20to%20the%20state%2C%20got%20stuck%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20seat%20sharing%2C%20with%20both%20sides%20refusing%20to%20budge%20from%20their%20respective%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26194005%2FOdisha-BJP-1024x444.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26194005%2FOdisha-BJP-1024x444.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26194005%2FOdisha-BJP-300x130.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F26194005%2FOdisha-BJP.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-703298%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22364%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20being%20said%20that%20the%20BJP%20asked%20for%20more%20seats%20citing%20its%20rise%20nationally%20and%20anti-incumbency%20against%20the%20BJD%2C%20which%20the%20latter%20party%20rejected.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40BJP4Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20contributing%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20talks%20was%20the%20insistence%20of%20leaders%20on%20both%20sides%20for%20certain%20assurances%20which%20either%20side%20found%20hard%20to%20concede.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnable%20to%20break%20the%20stalemate%20even%20after%20several%20rounds%20of%20negotiations%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20decided%20to%20call%20it%20quits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2022%2C%20after%20days%20of%20protracted%20negotiations%2C%20BJP%20state%20president%20Manmohan%20Samal%20announced%20that%20the%20party%20would%20fight%20alone%20on%20all%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20%E2%80%9Cto%20create%20a%20developed%20India%20and%20a%20developed%20Odisha%20under%20the%20visionary%20leadership%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHours%20later%2C%20BJD%20organisational%20secretary%20Pranab%20Prakash%20Das%20said%20that%20the%20regional%20party%20would%20not%20only%20contest%20all%20the%20seats%20on%20its%20own%20strength%20but%20also%20win%20more%20than%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthree-fourths%E2%80%9D%20majority%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20chief%20minister%20Patnaik.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20the%20know%20confide%20that%20in%20the%20initial%20round%20of%20talks%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20had%20almost%20reached%20an%20agreement%20under%20which%20the%20BJP%20was%20to%20get%20around%2047%20assembly%20seats%20and%2014%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%20This%20was%20keeping%20in%20mind%20their%20respective%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20BJP%20was%20more%20keen%20on%20increasing%20its%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20to%20reach%20the%20target%20of%20400%20at%20the%20all-India%20level%2C%20they%20wanted%20more%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20Odisha%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSimilarly%2C%20the%20BJD%2C%20being%20keen%20on%20winning%20a%20straight%20sixth%20term%20in%20power%20in%20the%20state%2C%20wanted%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20assembly%20seats.%20There%20was%20initial%20agreement%20over%20this%20arrangement%2C%20but%20later%2C%20some%20leaders%20on%20both%20sides%20started%20making%20demands%20which%20neither%20side%20was%20willing%20to%20meet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20being%20said%20that%20as%20the%20negotiations%20progressed%2C%20the%20BJP%20insisted%20on%20being%20given%2065%20assembly%20seats%20and%2015%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParty%20leaders%20argued%20that%20the%20BJP%20was%20on%20the%20rise%20all%20over%20the%20country%20and%20Odisha%2C%20where%20the%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20regime%20was%20bound%20to%20face%20anti-incumbency%20after%2024%20years%20of%20rule%2C%20was%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJD%2C%20however%2C%20found%20the%20demand%20ridiculous%20and%20rejected%20it%20outright.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20while%20the%20BJP%20sought%20assurances%20from%20the%20BJD%20on%20certain%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20including%20Cuttack%2C%20where%20it%20wanted%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfriendly%E2%80%9D%20candidate%2C%20the%20regional%20party%20asked%20for%20similar%20assurances%20from%20the%20BJP%20for%20chief%20minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik%E2%80%99s%20key%20aide%20V.K.%20Pandian%2C%20who%20joined%20the%20BJD%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20after%20taking%20voluntary%20retirement%20from%20the%20IAS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%2